{
  "texts": [
    "For example, in image recognition, it is common to set the values of all three RGB channels to zero as the base point.",
    "It is worth noting that the connection between DeepLIFT and Shapley value is established in DeepSHAP [14].",
    "DeepSHAP builds upon DeepLIFT and differs by using marginal distributed data as the base point.",
    "In essence, the two methods are equivalent when not considering the choice of base value.",
    "Ancona et al. [37] introduced a polynomial-time approximation for estimating Shapley values in deep neural networks by incorporating the concept of uncertainty propagation."
  ]
}